ry 17, 2017, 10:30am – 2:00pm (Lunch will be available between 11:30 AM and 1:00 PM) Where: Student Union Ballroom ( New venue with greater space!! ) Graduate Recruiters: To register and participate in the fair and/or to purchase an advertisement in the conference program, go to the Register for Conference page. The Graduate Schools and Programs Recruitment Fair engages McNair Scholars with representatives of many graduate schools and graduate programs. At our 2016 McNair Research Conference, over 40 graduate recruiters from more than 35 institutions explained and described their institutions opportunities for graduate studies.  We anticipate at least the same level of participation from graduate schools and programs for the 2017 conference. Below you can see the institutions that have already registered for this year's graduate fair. We have moved the fair to the Union to accommodate the large demand.  At the Fair, McNair Scholars and McNair staff can: Learn about admission requirements, scholarships and degree options from graduate schools Network with representatives from graduate schools from across Texas and the U.S. Meet with representatives from institutions you are already interested in Identify new institutions to consider for graduate studies.   Emporia State University Texas A&M International University of North Texas College of Engineering Georgia Institute of Technology Texas A&M University University of North Texas Health Science Center Henderson State University Texas State University University of Northern Colorado Iliff School of Theology Texas Tech University of Notre Dame Marquette University Texas Woman's University  University of Texas at Arlington  Miami University UC Irvine University of Texas at Austin Northern Arizona University UC San Diego     University of Texas at Dallas Northern Illinois University University of Cincinnati University of Texas at San Antonio NYU Tandon School of Engineering University of Houston Graduate College of Socia